## Migrating Flows <a href="#migrate" id="migrate"></a>

Migrate Flows from one WhatsApp Business Account (WABA) to another. Migration doesn't move the source Flows, it creates copies of them with the same names in the destination WABA.

**Notes:**

* You can specify specific Flow names to migrate, or choose to migrate all Flows in source WABA.
* Flows can only be migrated between WABAs owned by the same Meta business.
* If a Flow exists with the same name in the destination WABA, it will be skipped and the API will return an error message for that Flow. Other Flows in the same request will be copied.
* The migrated Flow will be published if the original Flow is published, otherwise it will be in draft state.
* New Flows under destination WABA will have new Flow IDs.

<mark style="color:green;">`POST`</mark>`https://hub.360dialog.io/api/v2/api/v2/partners/{partner_id}/waba_accounts/{waba_account_id}/flows/migrate_flows`

**Path Parameters**

| Name              | Type   | Description                 |
| ----------------- | ------ | --------------------------- |
| `partner_id`      | string | Your Partner ID             |
| `waba_account_id` | string | The ID of the WABA account. |

**Request Body**

| Name                     | Type           | Description                                                                                                                                          |
| ------------------------ | -------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `source_waba_account_id` | string         | <p>Source WhatsApp Business Account ID to copy flows from</p><p><br>Example: <code>exampleWA</code></p>                                              |
| `source_flow_names`      | array\[string] | <p>List of source flow names to migrate. If not provided, all flows will be migrated.</p><p></p><p>Example:[<code>"flow1","flow2"</code>]</p><p></p> |

```json
curl --request POST \
  --url https://hub.360dialog.io/api/v2/api/v2/partners/{partner_id}/waba_accounts/{waba_account_id}/flows/migrate_flows \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
  "source_waba_account_id": "exampleWA",
  "source_flow_names": [
    "flow1",
    "flow2"
  ]
}
